                            <comment id="14369502" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 19 Mar 2015 15:16:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, so it looks like &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7073&quot; title=&quot;Add an API to add a jar to a collection&amp;#39;s classpath&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7073&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7073&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; consolidated different types of plugin loading into one mechanism/container.  Some of them were thread safe (request handlers) and most were not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I didn&apos;t change everything to thread safe because it could have performance implications... there can be dozens or more lookups to all these plugins per request.  For now, I&apos;ve only enabled thread safety (for writes) for request handlers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
